# --------------------------------------------
# BACKUP & SECURITY BEST PRACTICES
# --------------------------------------------
#
# üîê SECURITY:
#   - NEVER commit your .env file to version control
#   - NEVER share your API keys publicly
#   - Keep your Firebase API key private (even though it's client-side)
#   - Enable Firebase App Check for production (optional but recommended)
#   - Regularly rotate your Gemini API key if exposed
#
# üíæ BACKUP YOUR CREDENTIALS:
#   - Store your .env file in a secure password manager (1Password, LastPass, etc.)
#   - Save a backup copy in an encrypted location (not in git!)
#   - Document which Firebase project belongs to which environment
#   - Keep a separate .env.production for deployment
#
# üìã RECOMMENDED BACKUP STRATEGY:
#   1. Copy your .env to a secure notes app
#   2. Save Firebase project name and URL
#   3. Save Gemini API key creation date
#   4. Document any custom Firebase rules or configuration
#   5. Export Firestore data regularly (Firebase Console ‚Üí Database ‚Üí Import/Export)
#
# üåç MULTIPLE ENVIRONMENTS:
#   - Development: .env (local testing)
#   - Staging: .env.staging (pre-production testing)
#   - Production: .env.production (live app)
#   - Use different Firebase projects for each environment
#
# üîÑ ROTATING API KEYS:
#   If you need to rotate keys (security breach, accidental exposure):
#
#   Firebase:
#     1. Create a new Firebase web app in same project
#     2. Update .env with new credentials
#     3. Delete old web app after testing
#
#   Gemini:
#     1. Visit https://makersuite.google.com/app/apikey
#     2. Create new API key
#     3. Update .env with new key
#     4. Delete old key after testing

# --------------------------------------------
# TROUBLESHOOTING
# --------------------------------------------
#
# ‚ùå "Firebase not initialized" error:
#    ‚Üí Check all VITE_FIREBASE_* variables are set
#    ‚Üí Ensure .env file is in project root
#    ‚Üí Restart dev server: npm run dev
#
# ‚ùå "Gemini API error" or "API key invalid":
#    ‚Üí Verify VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY is correct
#    ‚Üí Check you haven't exceeded free tier (1,500/day)
#    ‚Üí Generate new key: https://makersuite.google.com/app/apikey
#
# ‚ùå "Firestore permission denied":
#    ‚Üí Ensure security rules are published (see Setup Checklist #3)
#    ‚Üí Verify user is logged in
#    ‚Üí Check rules match the examples in README.md
#
# ‚ùå "Storage upload failed":
#    ‚Üí Enable Firebase Storage (see Setup Checklist #4)
#    ‚Üí Publish storage security rules
#    ‚Üí Verify image is under 5MB
#    ‚Üí Ensure file is valid image format
#
# ‚ùå Environment variables not loading:
#    ‚Üí All Vite env vars MUST start with VITE_
#    ‚Üí Restart dev server after changing .env
#    ‚Üí Check .env is in project root (same level as package.json)
#    ‚Üí Ensure no quotes around values (e.g., FOO=bar not FOO="bar")
#
# ‚ùå "Module not found" errors:
#    ‚Üí Run: npm install
#    ‚Üí Clear cache: rm -rf node_modules package-lock.json && npm install
#    ‚Üí Check Node.js version: node -v (need 18+)

